              prioritize privacy and security features to secure data access in
              your org, like SSO and fine-grained permissions.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2>When might Tableau be a better fit than Metabase?*</h2>
          <p></p>

          <ul class="checklist-outline">
            <li>
              You‚Äôre an enterprise-level company working with large, complex
              data sets, with a robust data team to manage your BI program.
            </li>

            <li>You have a very generous budget</li>

            <li>You only want some of your people querying your data</li>

            <li>
              You need advanced data visualization, including super
              sophisticated chart types, advanced analytics, predictive
              modeling, and integration with statistical languages like R and
              Python.
            </li>

            <li>
              You need extensive customization options for tailored dashboards
              and reports.
            </li>

            <li>You pledge allegiance to Salesforce</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="testimonial">
        <p>
          <b>*For the record...</b> Metabase also supports a number of happy enterprise-level
          customers for all their business intelligence needs - and for some, just
          the self-service part of their analytics program in addition to tools like
          Tableau. (We‚Äôre trying to present a somewhat balanced view here, but c‚Äômon,
          it‚Äôs still our website üòè)
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="testimonial">
        <p>
          ‚ÄúMetabase helped us achieve a nearly 90% decrease in monthly cost for
          our data platform while significantly improving our execution speed.
          Upon launch, we saw a nearly 90% reduction in ad-hoc requests to our
          team because of how easy and practical Metabase‚Äôs UI/UX is from a
          self-service perspective.‚Äù
        </p>

        <p class="author">Jason Turan</p>
        <p class="company">Head of Data &amp; Analytics at Alto</p>
      </div>

      <section
        class="m-0 mb-15 mb-lg-20 mx-auto p-0 center-xs container landing-page__ctas"
      >
        <h2 class="fs-8 fw-bold mx-auto my-0">Learn more about Metabase</h2>

        <div
          class="align-stretch d-flex flex-column flex-lg-row flex-nowrap gap-6 gap-lg-8 justify-content-between mt-8 mt-lg-13 ctas__cards"
        >
          <a
            class="bg-white border--blue-95 box-shadow-xs d-block m-0 p-4 p-lg-6 rounded-4 text-left ctas__cards__card"
            href="/case-studies/alto"
            title="Case Study - Read about how Alto switched from Tableau to Metabase"
          >
            <span
              class="bg-blue-95 blue-60 d-inline-block fs-15 fw-bolder m-0 px-3 py-2 rounded-3 text-uppercase"
              >Case Study</span
            >
            <h3 class="fs-10 fw-bold lh-base m-0 mt-4">
              Read about how Alto switched from Tableau to Metabase
            </h3>
          </a>

          <a
            class="bg-white border--blue-95 box-shadow-xs d-block m-0 p-4 p-lg-6 rounded-4 text-left ctas__cards__card"
            href="/learn/cheat-sheets/transition-guides/tableau-to-metabase"
            title="Transition cheat sheet - A smooth move from Tableau to Metabase"
          >
            <span
              class="bg-blue-95 blue-60 d-inline-block fs-15 fw-bolder m-0 px-3 py-2 rounded-3 text-uppercase"
              >Transition cheat sheet</span
            >
            <h3 class="fs-10 fw-bold lh-base m-0 mt-4">
              A smooth move from Tableau to Metabase
            </h3>
          </a>

          <a
            class="bg-white border--blue-95 box-shadow-xs d-block m-0 p-4 p-lg-6 rounded-4 text-left ctas__cards__card"
            href="/demo"
            title="Video demo - From zero to dashboard in 5 minutes"
          >
            <span
              class="bg-blue-95 blue-60 d-inline-block fs-15 fw-bolder m-0 px-3 py-2 rounded-3 text-uppercase"
              >Video demo</span
            >
            <h3 class="fs-10 fw-bold lh-base m-0 mt-4">
              From zero to dashboard in 5 minutes
            </h3>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="faq-container">
        <h4 class="faq-headline">Frequently asked questions</h4>

        <div class="faq">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <div>When is Metabase a better choice than Tableau?</div>
            <img alt="Chevron Blue" src="/images/chevron_blue.svg" width="14" />
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div>
              <p>
                Metabase is best suited for businesses that need a
                straightforward way for everyone in the team to self-serve
                analytics. BI that your team will actually enjoy using, at the
                right price for your scale.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-question">
            <div>When is Tableau a better choice than Metabase?</div>
            <img alt="Chevron Blue" src="/images/chevron_blue.svg" width="14" />
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div>
              <p>
                Credit where it‚Äôs due - Tableau can be a good fit for larger
                enterprises or orgs with more extensive data analysis needs,
                deep pockets, and a lower need for everyone in the org to be
                able to jump in and run their own reports. It‚Äôs got all the
                bells and whistles - and depending on the maturity of your org,
                your use case and needs, it may be more than you need.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-question">
            <div>Who uses Metabase over Tableau?</div>
            <img alt="Chevron Blue" src="/images/chevron_blue.svg" width="14" />
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div>
              <p>
                Metabase is trusted by over 80,000 companies with their
                analytics, from startups who need their first business
                intelligence tool through to Enterprises. Metabase open source
                is the go-to choice for founders and solo-developers to let
                their teams get answers from data on their own so they‚Äôre not
                running the same reports once a month. Metabase Pro and
                Enterprise is generally chosen by CTOs, CPOs, Heads of Data who
                have been there, done that with every other BI tool on the
                market and need a way to make self-service analytics <i
                  >actually</i
                > happen.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-question">
            <div>What use cases do Metabase and Tableau cover?</div>
            <img alt="Chevron Blue" src="/images/chevron_blue.svg" width="14" />
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div>
              <p>
                Metabase and Tableau both cater to internal analytics, as well
                as interactive embedded analytics for customers.
              </p><p>
                Metabase is ideal for quick, intuitive data exploration that
                lets people in your company click around in interactive
                dashboard and visualizations to learn from data, or create
                queries with or without SQL.
              </p><p>
                Tableau may be better suited for complex data analysis and
                putting detailed visualizations in front of customers.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-question">
            <div>
              What‚Äôs the differences in pricing between Metabase and Tableau?
            </div>
            <img alt="Chevron Blue" src="/images/chevron_blue.svg" width="14" />
